overview: The user initiated a comprehensive aesthetic review for their sleep
  questionnaire app, aiming to elevate its visual appeal from a generic template
  to a more professional and calming sleep-themed experience. The approach
  involved a detailed analysis of existing styles, followed by a multi-step
  implementation. Key changes included introducing a new OKLCH-based color
  palette, redesigning the main questionnaire form with decorative elements and
  an improved progress indicator, and enhancing core UI components like
  checkboxes, radio buttons, and sliders. All questionnaire sections were
  updated to reflect the new theme, replacing old gray boxes with cohesive
  card-style groupings and refined typography. During the review, a console
  error related to null values in input fields was also identified and fixed,
  ensuring smoother functionality. The outcome is a significantly more polished
  and thematically appropriate application, with a clear path for minor
  refinements identified in the final aesthetic review.
